  "text": "Neoplasms of the peripheral nerves such as schwannomas, neurofibromas and malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumors (MPNSTs) often occur as solitary lesions not involving the sural nerve. However, hereditary tumor syndromes, in particular neurofibromatosis (NF) 1 and 2, may affect the PNS in a more diffuse manner: NF1 with subcutaneous and large root diffuse neurofibromas can be associated with peripheral neuropathy [CITATION_1] , whereas NF2 is characterized by disseminated abnormal endoneurial Schwann cell proliferations, so called tumorlets [CITATION_2] .",
